data.description: The ever-elusive horse farm at the Delaware beaches is finally available! This property has the ideal farm setup for the horse enthusiast, nestled on 4.02 acres with a barn, pastures, riding ring, and plenty of storage. This home boasts easy one-level living, hardwood floors, vaulted ceilings, a wood-burning fireplace, a master suite with en-suite bath, soaking tub, separate shower, and walk-in closet, and two roomy guest bedrooms with a full guest bath. The eat-in kitchen features granite countertops and a bay window to let the natural light pour in and give you a fantastic view of the farm. Enjoy all of the outdoor living possible with a spacious front porch, a composite back deck, and a paver patio with a fire pit. Upgrades in this home include a full-house generator, a tankless water heater, a reverse osmosis water filter, and a fully fenced backyard. This farm is ready for your horses to move right in with a bright and airy barn with three matted stalls, each with Dutch doors, a concrete aisle, a large hay storage area that could also be converted to additional stalls, an enclosed feed and tack room, and an additional storage room, tractor shed, or run-in for the horses. The barn also features 200-amp electric and exterior lighting. The sand arena offers consistent riding throughout the year, and you can even take the horses for a swim in your private pond. This property has the ideal quiet setting, yet you're within easy access to Rt 113 and the beach areas.
